Class ProductEntityProcessor

java.lang.Object
de.dlr.proseo.api.prip.odata.ProductEntityProcessor
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.apache.olingo.server.api.processor.EntityProcessor, org.apache.olingo.server.api.processor.MediaEntityProcessor, org.apache.olingo.server.api.processor.Processor
@Component @Transactional public class ProductEntityProcessor extends Object implements org.apache.olingo.server.api.processor.EntityProcessor, org.apache.olingo.server.api.processor.MediaEntityProcessor
Retrieve product information from the prosEO metadata database (via the Ingestor component) and download product data from the prosEO Storage Manager
Author:
Dr. Thomas Bassler

    • readMediaEntity

      public void readMediaEntity(org.apache.olingo.server.api.ODataRequest request, org.apache.olingo.server.api.ODataResponse response, org.apache.olingo.server.api.uri.UriInfo uriInfo, org.apache.olingo.commons.api.format.ContentType responseFormat) throws org.apache.olingo.server.api.ODataApplicationException, org.apache.olingo.server.api.ODataLibraryException
      Download a product from the prosEO Storage Manager (any Storage Manager instance will do, because in the case of multiple copies of the product on various facilities, these should be identical); the Storage Manager is identified via the Facility Manager component

      This method does not actually return the data stream for the product, but rather redirects to the download URI at the Storage Manager

      Specified by:
      readMediaEntity in interface org.apache.olingo.server.api.processor.MediaEntityProcessor
      Parameters:
